<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1219">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Od2/2</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of the Treasury</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_PAJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Peters</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Counselor for the Department of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: In accordance with the
                            advice of your Department, communicated by telephone, I have this day
                            sent to the collector of customs at San Juan, P. R., a cablegram as
                            follows:</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>Supplementing Department’s wire 19th, have all parts <hi rend="italic">Odenwald</hi> thoroughly searched for arms, even
                                under coal. Report by wire to department for instructions and
                                withhold clearance until advised. War Department directed to
                                cooperate.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>You will be promptly advised of the collector’s reply.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PAJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">A. J. Peters</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>